ry intent flag. No multi-module handoff is required to expose the core failure; no OS/network/LLM dependency exists.","test_description":"Call the error-policy function/object with a parse-failure input and assert it returns the handled non-throw result plus telemetry-intent marker set as expected.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.75,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"In real process execution, malformed stdin does not crash the hook process and still emits the expected trace signal before exit.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly depends on real process execution, malformed stdin handling, crash/no-crash semantics, and pre-exit signaling. In-process fakes can hide subprocess/stdin/exit edge failures.","test_description":"Spawn the hook process as a real subprocess, send malformed bytes on stdin, assert non-crash behavior (controlled exit), and verify expected trace signal is emitted before process termination.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"A real hook invocation path (stdin -> parser -> trace sink) produces the expected trace artifact when malformed input is supplied.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The behavior names a real invocation path including stdin and trace sink artifact production, which crosses process/IO boundaries. Integration is too low because mocked stdin/sink may miss real artifact emission behavior.","test_description":"Invoke the hook through the real executable entrypoint, provide malformed stdin payload, and assert the trace artifact in the real sink/output location contains the expected parse-failure signal.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0.03,"